President Obama has signed an emergency declaration for the State of New York due to the conditions caused by the remnants of Tropical Storm Lee. This declaration allows the Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA) to coordinate disaster relief efforts and provide assistance to the affected areas. FEMA is authorized to mobilize resources and equipment to alleviate the impacts of the emergency, with 75 percent federal funding for emergency protective measures. Philip E. Parr has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected area. For more information, contact the FEMA news desk.